message.content:
This command establishes an encrypted connection using the SSH protocol to access a remote server with the specified IP address (ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com) and user (user). The command utilizes a private key file named "~/UserKey.pem" for authentication.

The options used in this command are:
-i: Specifies the private key file to use for authentication
-C: Enables compression of data over the encrypted connection
-L: Forward local port 25900 to the specified remote port (5900) on the localhost of the remote server

This command allows you to access the remote server and forward the local port to the remote one, enabling additional functionalities like remote desktop access.
